for democracy.

07:45.032 --> 07:47.933
The reason is not
because you need to be able

07:47.935 --> 07:50.869
to make private payments
in order to express yourself,

07:50.871 --> 07:54.573
but rather that in order
to inform yourself,

07:54.575 --> 07:56.842
you may need
to purchase information

07:56.844 --> 08:01.680
and that's the thing
that allows you to have
opinions worth expressing.

08:01.682 --> 08:04.115
Although I wouldn't say
David chaum was a cypherpunk,

08:04.117 --> 08:06.985
he definitely inspired
the cypherpunk movement.

08:06.987 --> 08:09.955
It's as if the cypherpunks
kind of came upon

08:09.957 --> 08:13.625
David chaum's tools,
