11:15.242 --> 11:16.908
That's all bitcoin really is.

11:16.910 --> 11:18.777
The key point here is that

11:18.779 --> 11:20.679
this a distributed ledger.

11:20.681 --> 11:22.180
There is no central server.

11:22.182 --> 11:23.715
All the other ledgers
that we have,

11:23.717 --> 11:25.684
all the banking ledgers,
all company ledgers,

11:25.686 --> 11:28.420
they all sit and reside
inside that company,

11:28.422 --> 11:30.288
which means they have
one point of attack.

11:30.290 --> 11:32.957
They can be hacked.
Jp Morgan was hacked

11:32.959 --> 11:34.993
by, you know, the cyberthieves
not so long ago.

11:34.995 --> 11:37.962
Home depot, target,
we've had all these companies
get hacked,

11:37.964 --> 11:41.966
precisely because there's
one central repository
of information.

11:41.968 --> 11:45.103
The bitcoin ledger resides,
on, you know,

11:45.105 --> 11:46.771
thousands of computers.

11:46.773 --> 11:48.173
You can't hack that.

11:48.175 --> 11:50.075
Every single transaction
is recorded,

11:50.077 --> 11:51.843
and once it is recorded
in the blockchain,

11:51.845 --> 11:53.912
it is there, it is permanent.

11:53.914 --> 11:56.948
It cannot be altered.
It cannot be changed,
so that you can read it.

11:56.950 --> 11:59.184
Now the identities
of the people are encrypted.

11:59.186 --> 12:00.785
The wallets are encrypted,

12:00.787 --> 12:03.021
so you don't know who
is spending the money,

12:03.023 --> 12:05.790
but you know that every
single bitcoin out there

12:05.792 --> 12:07.826
has a history,
you know where it's been,

12:07.828 --> 12:10.261
you know the different
addresses it's gone between.

12:12.865 --> 12:16.434
The most important pieces
of the bitcoin infrastructure

12:16.436 --> 12:17.836
are the miners.

12:17.838 --> 12:20.205
These are the computers
that are tasked

12:20.207 --> 12:22.874
with maintaining
the ledger of the blockchain

12:22.876 --> 12:25.243
to verify the information,
to update it,

12:25.245 --> 12:27.412
to make sure
that it is trustworthy.

12:27.414 --> 12:29.914
So how do we
incentivize them to do so?

12:29.916 --> 12:34.219
