through the process of
confirming transactions,

12:34.221 --> 12:37.355
they are simultaneously
being subjected to

12:37.357 --> 12:40.225
a very, very difficult
computing test.

12:40.227 --> 12:43.762
The bitcoin core protocol
is forcing them

12:43.764 --> 12:46.131
to look for a number.

12:46.133 --> 12:48.233
All of these miners
are ultimately competing

12:48.235 --> 12:51.136
to be the one that receives
that payout every ten minutes.

12:51.138 --> 12:53.171
But really that's
the secondary component.

12:53.173 --> 12:55.173
They're really being
rewarded with bitcoin,

12:55.175 --> 12:56.541
but what is
the more important task

12:56.543 --> 12:58.443
is the validation
and verification

12:58.445 --> 13:01.846
of transactions and
the maintaining of the ledger.

13:01.848 --> 13:05.083
Bitcoin, in being
the first to achieve

13:05.085 --> 13:10.054
this holy grail
of decentralized
value exchange

13:10.056 --> 13:12.423
that transfers
that process of trust

13:12.425 --> 13:16.127
to a collective agreement
around a body

13:16.129 --> 13:18.229
of independent computers

13:18.231 --> 13:21.032
who are compelled
by an incentive system

13:21.034 --> 13:22.400
to maintain that consensus

13:22.402 --> 13:25.069
and affirm the information
to be correct

13:25.071 --> 13:27.038
is incredibly liberating
because it means

13:27.040 --> 13:28.907
that we can do it without
all these intermediaries

13:28.909 --> 13:30.809
in all these different realms.

13:30.811 --> 13:33.845
The most important thing behind
bitcoin is not the currency.

13:33.847 --> 13:36.481
The key factor
is the blockchain.

13:36.483 --> 13:38.249
